The {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}} mentions Yatsunata only briefly, describing him as the "distant ancestor of the Kamitsukeno clan" without detailed genealogical information. However, according to the {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, he is identified as the son of {{ill|Toyoki Iribiko no Mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, who was a prince of {{ill|Emperor Sujin|ja|崇神天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
In the 5th year of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'s reign (October entry), Yatsunata was appointed as a general during the rebellion of {{ill|Sahohiko no Ō|ja|狭穂彦王|1=Sahohiko no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He was ordered to lead an assault on the fortress built by Sahohiko. Yatsunata set the fortress on fire, forcing Sahohiko to commit suicide. For this accomplishment, he was granted the title "Yamato Himuka Take Himuka Hiko Yatsunata."
== Descendant Clans ==
The {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft|qq=draft}} lists the following clans as descendants of Yatsunata: * Imperial Lineage ** Izumi Province, Tomi no Omi - Descended from "Yamato Himuka Take Himuka Hiko Yatsunata no Mikoto," son of {{ill|Toyoki Iribiko no Mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. ** Izumi Province, Karibe no Omi - Descended from "Yamato Himuka Take Himuka Hiko Yatsunata no Mikoto." During the reign of {{ill|Emperor Yūryaku|ja|雄略天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, they offered the village of Kari and received the surname "Karibe." * Uncertain Lineage ** Settsu Province, Abiko - Descended from "Yatsumata no Mikoto," son of {{ill|Toyoki Iribiko no Mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. ** Izumi Province, Abiko no Kimi - Descended from "Yamato Himuka Take Himuka Hiko Yatsunata no Mikoto," son of {{ill|Toyoki Iribiko no Mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
